    "Reading: a coefficient is significant at the 5% threshold if its confidence interval doesn't include the 0 vertical.",
    "We first visualize the dispersion of WVS and LLM answer distributions with multidimensional scaling (MDS).",
    "MDS is a linear technique used for scaling observations defined by a distance matrix.",
    "For each question, we compute a single MDS on the pairwise nEMD distances on all subpopulations (pooled LLMs and ground truth).",
